      <t:profileDesc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>
               The term stands for an extract from the Synaxarion (i.e., identified text), or a text close or similar to the Synaxarion notice.  
               Also, some Synaxarion manuscripts have a number of added notices, mostly short, written in a secondary hand(s) in the margins, extending the local commemorative practice.
               Sometimes they go with ʾarke-hymns (as they are in the regular Synaxarion), or are just ʾarke-hymns.
            </t:p>
            <t:p>Examples are:
               <t:list>
                  <t:item>
                     <t:p>
                        <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdmd002">Gāntā ʾAfašum, Dǝblā Yoḥannǝs Maṭmǝq, DMD-002</t:ref>;</t:p>
                  </t:item>
                  <t:item>
                     <t:p>
                        <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdd025">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy, Dabra Dāmmo ʾAbuna ʾAragāwi, DD-025</t:ref>;</t:p>
                  </t:item>
                  <t:item>
                     <t:p>
                        <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqsm024">Gulo Maḵadā, Qarsabar Qǝddus Mikāʾel, QSM-024</t:ref>;</t:p>
                  </t:item>
                  <t:item>
                     <t:p>
                        <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESsm011">Gulo Maḵadā, Sabayā Māryām, SM-011</t:ref>.</t:p>
                  </t:item>
               </t:list>
            </t:p>
         </t:abstract>
